{"questionId":"15521","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Three airport runways intersect to form a triangle, ABC. The length of AB is 3.1 km, AC is 2.6 km, and BC is 2.4 km.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/4b15b8e822b9f259ff958b53d2b198fdfec41185.png\"></p>\n<p>A&nbsp;company is hired to cut the grass that grows in triangle ABC, but they need to know the area.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the size, in degrees, of angle BÂC.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\cos \\,A = } \\right)\\,\\,\\frac{{{{2.6}^2} + {{3.1}^2} - {{2.4}^2}}}{{2\\left( {2.6} \\right)\\left( {3.1} \\right)}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>cos</mi>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>A</mi>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>2.6</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>3.1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>2.4</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>2.6</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>3.1</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n  